
UC46 View Patient Group Reports Use Case

An LHCP has authenticated him or herself in the iTrust Medical Records system [[requirements:uc2(UC2)]].

The LHCP requests a comprehensive report for all patients with a specified gender, age, and diagnosis . The LHCP is able to view the comprehensive group report .

    The LHCP chooses to view a report of all patients of a single or either gender, in a specified age range , with none, one, or more diagnoses.
    The LHCP can view of the comprehensive patient report for the specified group, including the information below.
        All patient demographic information (address, phone, etc.), see [[requirements:uc4(UC4)]] and [[requirements:df1Data Format 6.1]].
        All diagnoses, including those not normally viewable by the requesting LHCP, see [[requirements:uc11(UC11)]] and [[requirements:df5Data Format 6.5]].
        All designated HCPs (MIDs and Names), see [[requirements:uc6(UC6)]].
        All allergies, procedures, medications, office visits, and known relatives, see [[requirements:uc11(UC11)]] and [[requirements:df5Data Format 6.5]], [[requirements:df66.6]].
   The LHCP can download an XML file containing all patient information.

    The LHCP types an invalid age range and is prompted to try again.


 4601   View Group Report    LHCP    None    46    View    None    No  </textarea>
